comment_text: Earth is not warming at any alarming rate, nor is it warmer now than in the recent past. Actual climate science does not focus on narrow swaths of time. Romans had a warmer global temperature than we do. There is less co2 in the atmosphere than there was for most of earths 4.5 billion year history. Most important of all though is the FACT that co2 does not effect changes to climate through the greenhouse effect. The causal relationship between co2 and temperature is in reverse: rising temperatures affects increased co2 in the atmosphere, not the other way around. This key piece of evidence is ignored. Man made co2 is very real, but man made "climate change" is not.
